<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Males of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. zhaoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhaoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. zhaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from those of all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1878" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Portia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Portia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Portia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by having the longest embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia zhaoi Peng, Li &amp; Chen, 2003 A-D DL- 002 - 024 - 2012 A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F DL- 001 - 024 - 2012 G holotype deposited in the Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing E, G epigyne, ventral view F vulva dorsal view H, I male. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606783" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">6A</figureCitation>
); in addition, from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. erlangping" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erlangping">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. erlangping</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. fimbriata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. xishan" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xishan">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. xishan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. By the finger-shaped retrolateral tibial apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia zhaoi Peng, Li &amp; Chen, 2003 A-D DL- 002 - 024 - 2012 A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F DL- 001 - 024 - 2012 G holotype deposited in the Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing E, G epigyne, ventral view F vulva dorsal view H, I male. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606783" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">6A, B, D</figureCitation>
; see 7G in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" author="Wanless, FR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 124" refId="B14" refString="Wanless, FR, 1978. A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 34: 83 - 124, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" title="A revision of the spider genus Portia (Araneae: Salticidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/p.28739" volume="34" year="1978">Wanless (1978)</bibRefCitation>
); from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. quei" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. quei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the thicker ventral tibial apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Male and female genital anatomy of Portia zhaoi Peng, Li &amp; Chen, 2003 A-D DL- 002 - 024 - 2012 A palp, ventral view B, C palp, retrolateral view D palp, dorsal view E, F DL- 001 - 024 - 2012 G holotype deposited in the Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing E, G epigyne, ventral view F vulva dorsal view H, I male. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1068.72805.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606783" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">6B</figureCitation>
; see fig. 661 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peng, XJ" journalOrPublisher="Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" refId="B11" refString="Peng, XJ, Xie, LP, Xiao, XQ, Yin, CM, 1993. Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, Changsha" title="Salticids in China (Arachnida: Araneae)." year="1993">Peng et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. zhaoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhaoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. zhaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. labiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">P. labiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its longer copulatory ducts (Fig. 
